# Environment Configuration for MkDocs ChatBot Plugin
# Copy this file to .env and configure as needed
# IMPORTANT: .env should be in .gitignore and NOT committed!

# ==================================================
# Option 1: Using LM Studio (Local LLM) - CURRENT SETUP
# ==================================================
# LM Studio runs on http://127.0.0.1:11434 by default
#
# To fix CORS errors in LM Studio:
# 1. Open LM Studio
# 2. Go to Developer tab / Local Server
# 3. Enable "CORS" or "Allow CORS from browsers"
# 4. Add your docs URL to allowed origins if there's a specific field
# 5. Restart the local server
#
# LM Studio automatically handles CORS through its UI settings.

# ==================================================
# Option 2: Using OpenAI API
# ==================================================
# If you switch to OpenAI instead of LM Studio:
# 1. Get an API key from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# 2. Update mkdocs.yml to use OpenAI endpoint
# 3. Set your API key below:
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-api-key-here

# ==================================================
# Optional: Other Configurations
# ==================================================
# CHATBOT_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# CHATBOT_TEMPERATURE=0.7
